Event.info: OSINT - Qwerty Ransomware Utilizes GnuPG to Encrypt a Victims Files

Attribute.value: A new ransomware has been discovered that utilizes the legitimate GnuPG, or GPG, encryption program to encrypt a victim's files.  Currently in the wild, this ransomware is called Qwerty Ransomware and will encrypt a victims files, overwrite the originals, and the append the .qwerty extension to an encrypted file's name.
